# Capability: Model Router

**Commands:** `/route [task]` · `/compare [model A] vs [model B] on [task]` · `/estimate [task]`  
**Purpose:** Recommend the right model for each task based on cost-to-capability ratio. Integrate with ai-model-handoff when platform switching is warranted.

---

## Routing Philosophy

The most expensive model is not always the best model for a given task. Using a frontier model for a simple extraction task is like hiring a senior architect to paint a room — technically capable, unnecessarily costly. The router's job is to match task complexity to model capability with precision.

**Three routing dimensions:**
1. **Task complexity** — what level of reasoning does this genuinely require?
2. **Capability requirements** — does this task need specific tools, context length, or platform features?
3. **Cost tolerance** — is this a one-off task or a high-volume workflow?

---

## Model Tiers

### Tier 1 — Fast / Economical
Best for: Simple extraction, formatting, classification, summarization of short content, template filling, basic Q&A.

| Model | Input (per 1M) | Output (per 1M) | Context |
|---|---|---|---|
| Claude Haiku 3.5 | $0.80 | $4.00 | 200K |
| GPT-4o mini | $0.15 | $0.60 | 128K |
| Gemini Flash 2.0 | $0.10 | $0.40 | 1M |
| Mistral 7B (API) | $0.10 | $0.30 | 32K |

**Route here when:** The task requires reading and reformatting, extracting structured data, simple classification, short-form generation, or high-volume batch processing where cost is the primary constraint.

---

### Tier 2 — Mid-Tier / Balanced
Best for: Standard writing tasks, code generation, analysis, document summarization, multi-step instructions.

| Model | Input (per 1M) | Output (per 1M) | Context |
|---|---|---|---|
| Claude Sonnet 4.6 | $3.00 | $15.00 | 200K |
| GPT-4o | $2.50 | $10.00 | 128K |
| Gemini Pro 3.1 | $1.25 | $5.00 | 2M |
| Mistral Large | $2.00 | $6.00 | 128K |

**Route here when:** The task requires genuine reasoning, quality writing, code that will go to production, multi-document analysis, or structured outputs that need to be accurate and well-formatted.

---

### Tier 3 — Frontier / Premium
Best for: Complex multi-step reasoning, architecture decisions, long-horizon agent tasks, nuanced analysis, extended thinking.

| Model | Input (per 1M) | Output (per 1M) | Context |
|---|---|---|---|
| Claude Opus 4.6 | $15.00 | $75.00 | 200K |
| GPT-5 | $10.00 | $40.00 | 1M |
| Gemini Ultra 3.1 | $10.00 | $40.00 | 2M |
| DeepSeek R1 | $0.55 | $2.19 | 128K |

**Route here when:** The task has 3+ dependent reasoning steps, requires extended thinking, involves high-stakes decisions, or needs the best possible output quality where cost is secondary.

---

### Specialized Platforms
Tasks that belong on a specific platform regardless of tier.

| Platform | Route Here When | Cost Profile |
|---|---|---|
| Perplexity | Real-time web data required, citations needed | ~$5/1K queries (Pro) |
| Grok | X/social signal analysis, real-time discourse | Similar to Tier 2 |
| Cursor / Windsurf | Task lives in a codebase, multi-file changes needed | Credit-based |
| Claude Code | Terminal-native agentic coding, repo-level work | Per-token (Sonnet pricing) |
| Copilot | Task lives in M365 or GitHub repo | M365 license |
| Meta Llama (self-hosted) | Privacy-sensitive, air-gapped, high volume | Infrastructure cost only |

