## Routing Decision Matrix

Match the task description to the appropriate tier and platform:

### Task Type → Tier Mapping

| Task Type | Recommended Tier | Notes |
|---|---|---|
| Text extraction / parsing | Tier 1 | No reasoning required |
| Classification / tagging | Tier 1 | Simple decision tree |
| Template filling | Tier 1 | Formatting only |
| Short summarization (<2K input) | Tier 1 | Low complexity |
| Email drafting (standard) | Tier 1–2 | Depends on stakes |
| Code completion / snippets | Tier 2 | Quality matters |
| Long-form writing | Tier 2 | Balance quality/cost |
| Data analysis + narrative | Tier 2 | Reasoning required |
| Multi-document synthesis | Tier 2–3 | Depends on depth |
| Architecture decisions | Tier 3 | High stakes, complex |
| Multi-step agent tasks | Tier 3 | Dependencies compound |
| Extended reasoning / math | Tier 3 or DeepSeek R1 | R1 is cost-efficient here |
| Real-time research | Perplexity / Grok | Don't use frontier models for search |
| Codebase-wide changes | Cursor / Claude Code | Don't use chat models for IDE work |
| Large document corpus (>500K tokens) | Gemini (2M context) | Context window is the deciding factor |
| Privacy-sensitive at scale | Mistral / Llama self-hosted | Data sovereignty required |

